---
import CalculatorLayout from '../../layouts/CalculatorLayout.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'how-to-use', label: 'How to use this converter' },
  { id: 'cm-to-feet', label: 'cm to feet and inches' },
  { id: 'feet-to-cm', label: 'feet and inches to cm' },
  { id: 'reference',  label: 'Common height reference table' },
  { id: 'formulas',   label: 'Height conversion formulas' },
  { id: 'faq',        label: 'FAQs' },
];

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How tall is 5'10\" in cm?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "(5 × 12 + 10) × 2.54 = 177.8 cm" }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How do you convert cm to feet and inches?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Divide cm by 2.54 to get total inches. Then divide by 12 — the whole number is feet, the remainder is inches. Example: 175 cm ÷ 2.54 = 68.9 in = 5 ft 8.9 in." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How tall is 6 feet in cm?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "6 × 30.48 = 182.88 cm" }
    },
  ]
};
---

<CalculatorLayout
  title="Height Converter"
  metaTitle='Fast Height Converter | Convert cm, meters, feet & inches ᐅ'
  description="Convert height between centimetres, feet and inches, metres, and inches. Instant results with a full reference table."
  canonical="https://calculations.tools/conversion/height-converter"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  embedSlug="height-converter"
  schema={schema}
>

  <!-- CALCULATOR WIDGET -->
  <div slot="calculator">
    <section class="calculator-interface" id="hc-calculator">
      <div class="calculator-container">

        <div class="calculator-header">
          <h2>Instant Height Converter</h2>
          <p>Enter a value and select units — result updates instantly</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Quick conversions -->
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-white text-center mb-6">Quick Conversions</h3>
        <div id="hc-quick" class="lc-quick"></div>

        <!-- Inputs -->
        <div class="lc-inputs">
          <div class="input-group">
            <label for="hc-value">Value</label>
            <div class="hc-value-wrap">
              <input id="hc-value" type="number" value="180" placeholder="Enter value" />
              <input id="hc-in-part" type="number" placeholder="in" min="0" max="11" step="0.1" />
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="input-group">
            <label for="hc-from">From</label>
            <select id="hc-from"></select>
          </div>
          <div class="unit-swap-wrap">
            <button class="unit-swap" id="hc-swap" title="Swap units" aria-label="Swap units">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="#ffffff" width="16" height="16">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M7 16V4m0 0L3 8m4-4l4 4m6 0v12m0 0l4-4m-4 4l-4-4" />
              </svg>
            </button>
          </div>
          <div class="input-group">
            <label for="hc-to">To</label>
            <select id="hc-to"></select>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Result -->
        <div class="lc-result-box">
          <div class="result-label">Result</div>
          <div class="lc-result" id="hc-result">—</div>
          <div class="lc-result-desc" id="hc-result-desc"></div>
        </div>

        <!-- Common conversions -->
        <div class="lc-common-section">
          <h3 id="hc-common-title" class="lc-common-title"></h3>
          <div id="hc-common" class="lc-common-grid"></div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <script src="/js/height-converter.js" is:inline></script>
  </div>

  <!-- LONG-FORM CONTENT -->
  <div slot="content">
    <div class="seo-container">

      <h2 id="how-to-use">How to use this converter</h2>
      <p>Pick your "From" and "To" units from the dropdowns, then type a value. The result updates instantly. When you select "Feet &amp; Inches" as the from unit, a second input field appears for the inches part — enter the feet in the first box and the inches in the second. Use the quick conversion buttons at the top to jump straight to the most common height conversions.</p>

      <h2 id="cm-to-feet">cm to feet and inches</h2>
      <p>Converting centimetres to feet and inches takes three steps. Here is a worked example using 180 cm:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Divide by 2.54</strong> to get total inches: 180 ÷ 2.54 = 70.866 inches</li>
        <li><strong>Divide by 12</strong> to find feet: 70.866 ÷ 12 = 5 feet with a remainder</li>
        <li><strong>Multiply the remainder by 12</strong> to get inches: 0.866 × 12 = 10.4 inches</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Result: 180 cm = 5 ft 10.4 in</strong></p>
      <p>The key relationship to remember is that 1 inch = 2.54 cm exactly, and 1 foot = 12 inches = 30.48 cm.</p>

      <h2 id="feet-to-cm">feet and inches to cm</h2>
      <p>Converting feet and inches to centimetres is straightforward. Here is a worked example using 5'11":</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Convert feet to inches:</strong> 5 × 12 = 60 inches</li>
        <li><strong>Add the remaining inches:</strong> 60 + 11 = 71 total inches</li>
        <li><strong>Multiply by 2.54:</strong> 71 × 2.54 = 180.34 cm</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Result: 5'11" = 180.34 cm</strong></p>

      <h2 id="reference">Common height reference table</h2>
      <p>This table covers the most common human heights from 4'11" to 6'4".</p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Feet &amp; Inches</th><th>Centimetres</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>4'11"</td><td>149.9 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5'0"</td><td>152.4 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5'1"</td><td>154.9 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5'2"</td><td>157.5 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5'3"</td><td>160.0 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5'4"</td><td>162.6 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5'5"</td><td>165.1 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5'6"</td><td>167.6 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5'7"</td><td>170.2 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5'8"</td><td>172.7 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5'9"</td><td>175.3 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5'10"</td><td>177.8 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5'11"</td><td>180.3 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><td>6'0"</td><td>182.9 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><td>6'1"</td><td>185.4 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><td>6'2"</td><td>187.9 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><td>6'3"</td><td>190.5 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><td>6'4"</td><td>193.0 cm</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 id="formulas">Height conversion formulas</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>From</th><th>To</th><th>Formula</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>cm</td><td>inches</td><td>cm ÷ 2.54</td></tr>
          <tr><td>cm</td><td>feet (decimal)</td><td>cm ÷ 30.48</td></tr>
          <tr><td>inches</td><td>cm</td><td>in × 2.54</td></tr>
          <tr><td>feet</td><td>cm</td><td>ft × 30.48</td></tr>
          <tr><td>feet + inches</td><td>cm</td><td>(ft × 30.48) + (in × 2.54)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 id="faq">FAQs</h2>

      <h3>How tall is 5'10" in cm?</h3>
      <p>5'10" equals <strong>177.8 cm</strong>. Calculation: (5 × 12 + 10) × 2.54 = 70 × 2.54 = 177.8 cm.</p>

      <h3>How tall is 170 cm in feet?</h3>
      <p>170 cm equals <strong>5 ft 6.9 in</strong>. Calculation: 170 ÷ 2.54 = 66.929 inches = 5 feet and 6.929 inches.</p>

      <h3>How tall is 6 feet in cm?</h3>
      <p>6 feet equals <strong>182.88 cm</strong>. Calculation: 6 × 30.48 = 182.88 cm.</p>

      <h3>How do I convert my height from cm to feet?</h3>
      <p>There are two approaches. For decimal feet, divide your height in cm by 30.48. For feet and inches, first divide by 2.54 to get total inches, then divide by 12 — the whole number is your feet, and the remainder is your inches. For example, 175 cm ÷ 30.48 = 5.741 ft, or as feet and inches: 175 ÷ 2.54 = 68.9 in = 5 ft 8.9 in.</p>

      <h3>What is the average height?</h3>
      <p>The world average adult male height is approximately <strong>171 cm (5'7")</strong> and the average adult female is approximately <strong>159 cm (5'2.5")</strong>. These figures vary significantly by country — Dutch men average around 183 cm, while the global range spans from under 160 cm to over 175 cm for men.</p>

      <h3>How many cm is one inch?</h3>
      <p>One inch equals exactly <strong>2.54 cm</strong>. This is an exact definition established by international agreement in 1959, making all inch/cm conversions precise rather than approximate.</p>

    </div>
  </div>

</CalculatorLayout>

<style is:global>
  .hc-value-wrap { display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .hc-value-wrap input { flex: 1; min-width: 0; }
</style>
